SIMPLE: boson
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: boson
<hw>bo"son</hw> <pr>(b⟦omac⟧"z⟦ocr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From S.
N. <ets>Bose</ets>, an Indian physicist.]</ety> <fld>(Physics)</fld>
<def>A fundamental particle that obeys Bose-Einstein statistical rules,
but not the Pauli exclusion principle; the spin value of a boson is
always an integer. Examples of bosons are alpha particles, photons, and
those nuclei which have an even mass number.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>boson</ent>⟦br⟧

